RIFTSMUD CODING WIZARD HANDBOOK

WHO THIS IS FOR
Builders and coders who write rooms, NPCs, weapons, and armor for
AetherMUD using QCS and manual LPC editing.

POSITION AND ROLE
  position: creator (legacy alias: immortal)
  wiz_role: coding (synced automatically from position)

TOOLS YOU MUST HOLD
  Staff of Creation, held in inventory
Granted on promotion. QCS does not work without this staff in inventory.
Also: review - apprentice coding queue (list/read/mark implemented).

COMMAND ACCESS
Coding wizards do NOT get the broad creator command path (no standalone
update, eval, or qcs on the command line). The QCS builder verbs below
are the exception: they work directly, without a prefix, for any wizard
holding the staff of creation.

You CAN also use ambassador file tools for manual editing:
  ed, cat, ls, cd, pwd, and related file shell commands
  workroom

QCS BUILDER WORKFLOW
You must be inside your realm: /realms/<yourname>/

  create room <dir> <file>
  create npc <file>
  create weapon <file>
  create armor <file>
  modify here <property> <value>
  modify <file> <property> <value>
  add exit <direction> <path>
  add <npcfile> to here
  delete <object>
  about <file|here>
  more <file|here>

Older alternate form, still supported: build <verb> ... (e.g. build create
room east test1). Prefer the direct verbs above for everyday building.

clone <path> and purge <id> are separate staff-only commands, already
direct (no prefix), granted by holding the staff of creation.

Files are written under:
  /realms/<yourname>/area/room/
  /realms/<yourname>/area/npc/
  /realms/<yourname>/area/weap/
  /realms/<yourname>/area/armor/

Each modify auto-recompiles the target file.

DIRECTORY ACCESS
  Your QCS sandbox: /realms/<yourname>/area/
  Your workroom: /realms/<yourname>/workroom
  Shared game areas: only paths assigned by a Domain or Admin wizard
  Per-realm access control: /realms/<name>/adm/access.c

LPC RULES (FluffOS 2.9)
  Declare ALL variables at the top of each function block (C89).
  Use /* */ comments only, not //.
  Do not describe spawned NPCs in set_long(); use reset() spawns.
  Smell and listen text only on explicit smell/listen commands.

KEY INHERIT PATHS
  Rooms: ROOM (from rooms.h)
  Rifts NPCs: /std/rifts_npc
  Weapons: /std/weapon
  Armor: /std/armour

YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES
  Build and maintain assigned areas in your realm or assigned domain
  Follow Rifts tone, Palladium accuracy, and lib conventions
  Test content in your realm before requesting a domain merge
  Report blockers to your Domain wizard

NOT YOUR JOB
  Promoting or demoting anyone
  Granting player skills or tattoos (Roleplay wizard)
  Managing /domains/ structure (Domain wizard)
  Editing core std files without admin approval

SEE ALSO
  help ed *creator general
